. *If we use both proxies bias is not solved
. 
. *As we can see, the standard errors of the estimated coefficients are much
>  smaller in the large sample than in the small sample. Moreover, the IV es
> timator removes the bias present in the OLS estimator caused by measuremen
> t error. Finally, when the instrument has larger measurement error, the IV
>  estimator has a larger standard deviation, indicating lower precision.
. 
. *Running IV regressions "without instruments"
. clear all

. 
. *Here I set seed to 1000 so that the task can be replicated
. set seed 1000

. 
. set obs 3000
Number of observations (_N) was 0, now 3,000.

. 
. gen x1 = invnorm(uniform())

. 
. foreach i of numlist 100 3000 {
  2.         tempfile  arthurmc`i'
  3.         local j = 1
  4.         while `j' <= 1000 {
  5.                 quietly {
  6.                         
.                         preserve
  7.                         sample `i', count
  8.                         noisily di "." _continue
  9.         
.                         gen u = invnorm(uniform())
 10.                         gen s1 = invnorm(uniform())
 11.                         gen s2 = invnorm(uniform())
 12. 
.                         *Heterocedasticity errors
.                         gen e1 = u + exp(x1)*s1
 13.                         gen e2 = u + exp(-x1)*s2
 14. 
.                         *Triangular model
.                         gen y2 = 1 + x1 + e2
 15.                         gen y1 = 1 + y2 + x1 + e1
 16. 
.                         *First stage regression
.                         /*
>                         x1 can be used as Z because satisfies both assumpt
> ions
>                         - Relevance cov(x1,y2) != 0
>                         - Exogeneity con(x1, u) = 0
>                         */
.                         reg y2 x1
 17.                         predict e2hat, resid
 18. 
.                         *Create the Lewbel instrument
.                         sum x1
 19.                         gen z = (x1 - r(mean))*e2hat
 20. 
.                         *Run IV
.                         ivregress 2sls y1 x1 (y2 = z)
 21.                         matrix b1 = e(b)
 22.                         
.                         reg y1 x1 y2 
 23.                         matrix b2 = e(b)
 24.                         
.                         svmat b1, name(ols_consistent`i')
 25.                         svmat b2, name(ols_inconsistent`i')
 26.                         
.                         collapse (mean) ols_consistent* ols_inconsistent*
 27.                         
.                         if `j' > 1 {
 28.                                 append using `arthurmc`i''
 29.                         }
 30.                         
.                         save `arthurmc`i'', replace
 31.                         restore
 32.                         
.                         local j = `j' + 1
 33.                 }
 34.         }       
 35. }
